# Feedback Structure

The SEO analysis system returns structured feedback objects which are rendered in the UI:

## Feedback Object Format
```javascript
{
  criteria: "keyword_in_title", // The assessment criteria name
  score: 0.85,                  // Score between 0-1 (higher is better)
  description: "The keyword is present in the title",
  actual: "Current: 2 times",   // Optional current state
  recommended: "Recommended: 1-2 times" // Optional recommendation
}
```

## Feedback Categories
1. **Title Feedback**: Assessment of page title SEO elements
2. **Meta Feedback**: Assessment of meta description SEO elements
3. **Content Feedback**: Assessment of main content SEO elements

## Score Visualization
- Each feedback item has an icon based on score:
  - Score ≥ 0.8: Check circle (success)
  - Score ≥ 0.5: Warning triangle (warning)
  - Score < 0.5: X circle (danger)

The feedback structure is designed to be easily extensible for new SEO criteria.
